Description

The mission_hospital dataset provides information on 248 Patients of Mission Hospital. The dataset provides patient information including : basic background, medical history and preliminary investigation conducted upon admission. Information about the length of hospitalization and cost to the hospital is also provided.

Objective and Approach

Mission Hospital seeks to develop a predictive model to predict the cost expected to be incurred by the hospital at time of admission. The predictive model would assist the hospital management to negotiate package pricing with the state CGHS with increased accuracy and decreased risk to the hospital. The analyst will build multiple predictive models using Linear Regression, Decision Tree and Random Forest algorithms.
